Reading material: We know that $4x-2x+x=(4-2+1)x=3x$. Similarly, if we consider $(a+b)$ as a whole, then $4(a+b)-2(a+b)+(a+b)=(4-2+1)(a+b)=3(a+b)$. The "whole concept" is an important thinking method in solving problems in secondary school teaching, and it is widely used in the simplification and evaluation of polynomials.  
$(1)$ Considering $(m-n)^{2}$ as a whole, the result of combining $3(m-n)^{2}-4(m-n)^{2}+3(m-n)^{2}$ is ______;  
